# Cursor rules — NWN:EE Aurora Module Project

## Project context

This is a Neverwinter Nights: Enhanced Edition module project targeting a persistent world server. The Aurora Toolset is the visual authoring environment for areas, dialogs, blueprints, and module properties. Nasher manages the build pipeline. NWScript (`.nss`) is the scripting language. PostgreSQL backs the persistent world. A TypeScript MCP server exposes tooling to AI assistants.

## Directory structure

```
src/scripts/     — NWScript source (.nss) — PRIMARY development surface
src/areas/       — Area GFF JSON (generated by nasher unpack — do not hand-edit)
src/blueprints/  — Creature/item/placeable JSON (generated by nasher unpack)
src/dialogs/     — Dialog GFF JSON (generated by nasher unpack)
src/2da/         — Custom 2DA rows only (not full base-game tables)
src/tlk/         — Custom talk-table entries
database/        — PostgreSQL migrations and seed data
docker/          — Server deployment compose files
tools/mcp/nwn-mcp/ — Active MCP server (TypeScript)
tools/testing/   — Python mock test harness
docs/            — Design docs, ADRs, release notes
```

## NWScript conventions

### File prefixes

- `inc_*` — shared constants and utilities (included by other scripts)
- `db_*` — database repository wrappers (all NWNX SQL calls live here)
- `sys_*` — gameplay systems (death, login, quest, economy)
- `evt_*` — event dispatch helpers (thin wires to sys_ modules)
- `qst_*` — quest-specific logic
- `adm_*` — DM/admin tools
- `mod_on_*` — module event entry points
- `plc_*`, `cre_*`, `trg_*` — object-specific scripts

### Architecture rules

- Keep event scripts thin: `mod_on_client_enter.nss` calls `Event_DispatchClientEnter()`, not business logic.
- All SQL/NWNX calls go through `db_*` includes — never scatter raw queries in gameplay scripts.
- Keep pure-logic functions (arithmetic, state checks) separate from engine calls so they can be mirrored in Python tests.
- `DelayCommand` and `AssignCommand` go in event or object scripts, not in include files.

### Naming patterns

```c
// Constant in include
const int QUEST_STATE_INTRO = 1;

// Pure function (testable without NWN runtime)
int Quest_CanAdvance(int nState, int bHasItem, int nFactionRep)

// Engine wrapper
int Quest_CanAdvance_ForPC(object oPC)

// Module event handler prefix
void Event_DispatchClientEnter(object oPC)
```

## TypeScript (MCP server) conventions

The active MCP server lives in `tools/mcp/nwn-mcp/`. Code style:
- Strict TypeScript — no `any` unless wrapping raw schema parse results.
- Use `execa` (not `child_process.exec`) for shell commands.
- Validate every file path through `resolveWorkspacePath()` / `safeArgs()` before use.
- Tool handlers return `{ content: [{ type: "text", text: JSON.stringify(result, null, 2) }] }`.
- Gate dangerous operations with explicit permission flags from config.

## Python test conventions

Tests live in `tools/testing/script-tests/`. Rules:
- Import mock runtime: `import nwscript_mock as nwn`.
- Call `nwn.reset_state()` in every `setUp()`.
- Mirror NWScript pure functions exactly — same parameter names, same logic.
- No pytest-specific features; tests must also pass with `python3 -m unittest`.

## SQL migration conventions

- Name: `NNNN_short_description.sql` (zero-padded sequence).
- Wrap in `BEGIN; ... COMMIT;`.
- Add explicit constraints and indexes.
- Never edit a deployed migration — create a new one.

## What to avoid

- Hand-editing `src/areas/`, `src/blueprints/`, or `src/dialogs/` JSON files — use Aurora Toolset, then `nasher unpack`.
- Committing `.mod`, `.hak`, `.erf`, or `.tlk` files to git.
- Adding raw SQL to quest or placeable scripts — route through `db_*` includes.
- Running `nasher install` without confirming it will write to the user's NWN_HOME directory.
- Running `docker compose down -v` — it destroys persistent database volumes.
- Upgrading pinned tool versions (NWN:EE build, Nasher, Blender, NeverBlender) without team review.

## Toolchain versions (pinned)

- NWN:EE: `89.8193.37`
- Nasher: `1.1.2`
- neverwinter.nim: `2.1.2`
- Blender: `4.0.0` (not latest — NeverBlender requires this exact version)
- NeverBlender: `4.1.0`

## Common commands

```bash
nasher unpack                  # import Aurora Toolset changes into src/
nasher pack module             # build .mod artifact
./scripts/run-script-tests     # run Python mock tests
./scripts/compile-scripts      # compile NWScript (needs NWN_ROOT)
./tools/smoke-test.sh          # validate project layout
```

## MCP server tools (prefer over raw shell)

Use MCP tools when available:
- `nwn.project.inspect` — project health check
- `nwn.script.compile` — compile one .nss file with diagnostics
- `nwn.script.find_symbol` — find a function definition
- `nwn.nasher.build` — run nasher pack safely
- `nwn.docs.search` — search project documentation
- `nwn.docs.add_decision` — create an ADR in docs/ADR/
